Babak is a legend, you should take CS70

---------------------------

Just to add, I've heard mixed things about Weaver (not so great in terms of grading and workload).

Also, you should consider your other classes as well (for example, if you have a heavy project workload with other CS classes, taking CS 70 would be better and vice-versa).

Another review for Nick. I took 61c with him and I highly recommend him! (I am currently taking 161 with him too!) Well, it really depends on how well you can balance the workload (one of his project might involve Go lang which is probably new to you). Also, some might find that the extra info (related to security) he put on 61C slides are really annoying, but IMO it's really interesting.

history.content: Hi, I'm trying to decide between taking CS70 and CS61C next semester. I'm a sophomore but I was hoping if anyone had any advice on which professors for each course is better. CS70 will be taught by Babak Ayazifar, Satish Rao. CS61C will be taught by Nicholas Weaver. Does anyone have any opinions?
